{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881096386,"sessionID":"ses_2853d982fffe05VvFNh3Ebe799","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac300f6001c9MXsxsv9ImgC7","messageID":"msg_d7ac2eee2001QMmV117PN7zAtB","sessionID":"ses_2853d982fffe05VvFNh3Ebe799","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_78d18072c1c24072a3ebf0f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Chart Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: manifests/charts/base/\n13: ├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n14: ├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n15: ├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n16: ├── crds/\n17: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n18: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n19: └── templates/\n20:     ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions\n21:     ├── redis-secret.yaml               # Redis password Secret\n22:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n23:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n24:     ├── rbac/\n25:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n26:     ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router RBAC\n27:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ### Component Diagram\n31: \n32: ```\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                    Helm Chart (agentcube)                        │\n35: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n36:                               │\n37:                               │ helm install/upgrade\n38:                               ▼\n39: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                   Kubernetes Cluster                             │\n41: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐ │\n42: │  │     Router       │  │ WorkloadManager  │  │   Volcano     │ │\n43: │  │  Deployment      │  │   Deployment     │  │   Scheduler   │ │\n44: │  │  + Service       │  │   + Service      │  │  (optional)   │ │\n45: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────────┘ │\n46: │           │                      │                               │\n47: │           └──────────┬───────────┘                               │\n48: │                      │                                           │\n49: │           ┌──────────▼───────────┐                               │\n50: │           │   Redis Secret        │                               │\n51: │           │   (password store)    │                               │\n52: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n53: │                                                                   │\n54: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n55: │           │   RBAC Resources      │                               │\n56: │           │   (SA, Role, Binding) │                               │\n57: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n58: │                                                                   │\n59: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n60: │           │      CRDs             │                               │\n61: │           │  agentruntimes,       │                               │\n62: │           │  codeinterpreters     │                               │\n63: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n64: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### Integration Points\n68: \n69: - **Redis**: External dependency for session storage (address/password from values)\n70: - **Volcano Scheduler**: Optional component for advanced scheduling\n71: - **RBAC**: WorkloadManager requires cluster-wide permissions; Router RBAC is optional\n72: - **CRDs**: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n73: \n74: ## Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### Chart.yaml Metadata\n77: \n78: ```yaml\n79: apiVersion: v1\n80: name: agentcube\n81: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n82: version: 0.1.0\n83: appVersion: \"1.0.0\"\n84: keywords:\n85:   - agent\n86:   - sandbox\n87:   - kubernetes\n88:   - volcano\n89: maintainers:\n90:   - name: Volcano Authors\n91:     email: volcano-sh@googlegroups.com\n92: home: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n93: sources:\n94:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### values.yaml Configuration Tree\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: # Global settings\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 884. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n├── crds/\n│   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n│   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","time":{"start":1775881096369,"end":1775881096384}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881096388,"sessionID":"ses_2853d982fffe05VvFNh3Ebe799","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac306bb001LVD1RYstlg8GYI","messageID":"msg_d7ac2eee2001QMmV117PN7zAtB","sessionID":"ses_2853d982fffe05VvFNh3Ebe799","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_97806f1784de45b084477370","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `manifests`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n21: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n22: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n23: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount metadata\n26: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n27: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n29:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n30:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n31:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n34: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is applied\n35: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is executed\n36: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount metadata\n39: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n40: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n41: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n42:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n43:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n44:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount creation\n47: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n48: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n49: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount metadata\n52: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n53: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n55:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n56:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n57:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: scheduler`\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ### REQ-031.2: ClusterRole Manifests\n62: \n63: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRole manifests defining permissions for WorkloadManager and Volcano Scheduler.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole creation\n66: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n67: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n68: - **THEN** a ClusterRole named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n71: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n72: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n74:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n75:   - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n76:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole extension resources\n79: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n80: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n82:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n83:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n84:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole warm pool status\n87: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n88: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n90:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n91:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n92:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n95: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n96: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n98:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n99:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n100:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 578. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n\n**Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881096371,"end":1775881096386}}}}
