l}` |\n536: | Permission denied | 1 | `RBAC: User '{user}' cannot {verb} {resource}` |\n537: | Invalid manifest syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Dependencies\n542: \n543: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n544: |---------|---------|---------|\n545: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | RBAC API (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n546: | kubectl | ≥1.21 | Manifest application and validation |\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ## Acceptance Checklist\n551: \n552: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/namespace.yaml` — Namespace manifest with correct labels\n553: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n554: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/router.yaml` — Router ServiceAccount\n555: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n556: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRole with all permissions\n557: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole with scheduling permissions\n558: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n559: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n560: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/roles/router.yaml` — Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n561: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rolebindings/router.yaml` — Router RoleBinding\n562: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml` — Combined manifest with correct ordering\n563: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac-cleanup.yaml` — Cleanup manifest with reverse ordering\n564: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh` — Validation script\n565: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/README.md` — Usage documentation\n566: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/` succeeds without errors\n567: - [ ] Validation script reports all resources as healthy\n568: - [ ] Cleanup removes all RBAC resources correctly\n569: - [ ] Multi-namespace deployment works correctly\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Open Questions\n574: \n575: 1. Should RBAC manifests support fine-grained permission customization through overlay files?\n576: 2. Should the validation script integrate with CI/CD pipelines for automated RBAC testing?\n577: 3. Should RBAC manifests include PodSecurityPolicy or PodSecurityStandard bindings?\n578: 4. Should there be separate RBAC profiles (minimal, standard, full) for different security requirements?\n\n(End of file - total 578 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"│   ├── router.yaml\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n├── clusterroles/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n├── clusterrolebindings/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n├── roles/\n│   └── router.yaml\n├── rolebindings/\n│   └── router.yaml\n├── rbac.yaml              # Combined manifest\n├── rbac-cleanup.yaml      # Cleanup manifest\n└── validate-rbac.sh       # Validation script\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881113647,"end":1775881113659}}}}
